data.name: fckF1Description.Text
data.value: Have you ever hit the F1 key only to bring up unhelpful built-in help popups and controls? Annoying AF, isn't it? Use this control to break the stupid Windows help function so that it never gets in the way of what you're doing. Note: this only interferes with Windows help and does NOT disable the F1 key (which we need for gaming and other functions)

data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value: As long as the old DOS prompt hangs around, it's necessary to get into a CMD window now and then, but these days, only the PowerShell context window is still there. Sometimes we need a CMD window and it needs to be admin level. This puts the context menu back in Explorer with a right click on folder.
